HEADWORD: Hydria
<hw>Hy"dri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<?/.]</ety> <fld>(Gr. Antiq.)</fld> <def>A water jar; esp., one with a
large rounded body, a small neck, and three handles. Some of the most
beautiful Greek vases are of this form.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

